<tool id="groot_report" name="Groot report" version="@VERSION@+galaxy0" profile="22.05">
    <description>to generate a resistome profile</description>
    <macros>
        <token name="@VERSION@">1.1.2</token>
    </macros>
    <xrefs>
        <xref type="bio.tools">groot</xref>
    </xrefs>
    <requirements>
        <requirement type="package" version="@VERSION@">groot</requirement>
    </requirements>
    <command detect_errors="exit_code"><![CDATA[
    groot report
    --bamFile '$input_bam'
    -c '$coverage'
    > '$output_report'

]]></command>
    <inputs>
        <param name="input_bam" type="data" format="bam" label="Input bam file"/>
       <param name="coverage" type="float" min="0" max="1.0" value="0.97" label="Coverage needed to report an ARG" />
    </inputs>
    <outputs>
        <data name="output_report" format="tabular" label="${tool.name} on ${on_string}"/>
    </outputs>
    <tests>
        <test>
            <param name="input_bam" value="groot.bam" />
            <param name="coverage" value="0.97" />
            <output name="output_report" file="groot.report" />
        </test>
    </tests>
    <help>
**What it does**

The report subcommand is used to processes graph traversals and generate a resistome profile for a sample

    </help>
    <citations>
        <citation type="doi">https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1217889</citation>
    </citations>
</tool>
